HEADWORD: Ileus
<hw>Il"e*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/,
<?/, fr. <?/ to roll up.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A morbid
condition due to intestinal obstruction. It is characterized by complete
constipation, with griping pains in the abdomen, which is greatly
distended, and in the later stages by vomiting of fecal matter. Called
also <altname>ileac passion</altname> <it>or</it> <altname>iliac
passion</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

